exports[`parseConversation fixture snapshots > parses simple-text 1`] = `
{
  "conversation": {
    "branches": [
      [
        {
          "attachments": [],
          "blocks": [
            {
              "text": "What vegetables grow well in partial shade? I have a north-facing bed that only gets about four hours of sun.",
              "type": "text",
            },
          ],
          "createdAt": "2026-05-14T09:12:03.512847Z",
          "files": [],
          "id": "a1c3e5f7-2b4d-4a6c-8e0f-1d3b5a7c9e02",
          "parentId": null,
          "sender": "human",
          "updatedAt": "2026-05-14T09:12:03.512847Z",
        },
        {
          "attachments": [],
          "blocks": [
            {
              "text": "Four hours of sun is enough for plenty of crops. Leafy greens and many root vegetables actually prefer some shade.

| Crop | Sun needed | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Lettuce | 3–4 h | Bolts slower in shade |
| Spinach | 3–4 h | Sow early spring |
| Radishes | 4 h | Ready in ~30 days |
| Chard | 4 h | Cut-and-come-again |

A simple sowing plan:

\`\`\`text
March:  spinach, radishes
April:  lettuce, chard
May:    succession-sow lettuce every 2 weeks
\`\`\`

Avoid fruiting crops (tomatoes, peppers, squash) — they need 6–8 hours.",
              "type": "text",
            },
          ],
          "createdAt": "2026-05-14T09:12:08.930214Z",
          "files": [],
          "id": "b4e8d2f6-1a3c-4e5b-9d7f-8c2a6b0e4d19",
