            {
              "summaries": [
                "Calculating wall area minus doors and window",
                "Converting coverage into litres for two coats",
              ],
              "thinking": "Wall area: perimeter = 2 × (6 + 1.2) = 14.4 m. Wall area = 14.4 × 2.4 = 34.56 m².

Subtract openings: three doors ≈ 3 × (0.76 × 2.0) = 4.56 m². One window ≈ 1.2 × 1.0 = 1.2 m². Net ≈ 28.8 m².

